etymologies: late 19th century; earliest use found in The Oregonian. From scientific Latin Titanosaurus Titanosaurus: see -saur

definitions: Any of various long-necked Cretaceous dinosaurs of the group Titanosauria, comprising sauropods related to the genus Titanosaurus.

notes.text: The titanosaurs included some of the largest known dinosaurs and were the only sauropods to survive into the late Cretaceous.
